<h3 class="title is-4">Model Selection</h3>
<p class="subtitle is-6">Choose the AI models this bot will use for chat and document processing.</p>
<hr>

<div class="field">
    <label class="label" for="default_model">
        <span class="icon-text">
            <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-brain"></i></span>
            <span>Default Chat Model</span>
        </span>
    </label>
    <div class="control">
        <div class="select is-fullwidth is-medium">
            <select name="default_model" id="default_model">
                {% for model in chatModels %}
                    <option value="{{ model.id }}" {{ model.id == bot.default_model ? 'selected' : '' }}>
                        {{ model.id }}
                    </option>
                {% else %}
                    <option value="">No chat models available</option>
                {% endfor %}
            </select>
        </div>
    </div>
    <p class="help">This model will handle all general chat conversations and responses for this bot.</p>
</div>

{% if chatModels|length > 0 %}
<div class="notification is-info is-light mt-5">
    <h5 class="title is-6">
        <span class="icon-text">
            <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i></span>
            <span>Model Information</span>
        </span>
    </h5>
    <div class="content is-small">
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Different models have varying capabilities, response speeds, and costs.</li>
            <li><strong>Context:</strong> Some models handle longer conversations better than others.</li>
            <li><strong>Switching:</strong> You can change the model anytime. Changes will apply to new conversations.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>
{% endif %} 